1.name: Barge chemical tanker
1.desc: A barge equipped to transport liquid chemicals.

2.name: Coaster chemical tanker
2.desc: A coaster vessel equipped to transport liquid chemicals.

3.name: Dry bulk carrier
3.desc: Vessel designed to carry dry bulk (expellers).

4.name: Deep sea chemical tanker
4.desc: An ocean-going vessel equipped to transport liquid chemicals.

5.name: Gas tanker
5.desc: A vessel equipped to transport gas.

7.name: Car with caravan
7.desc: A caravan towed by a car.

8.name: Container ship
8.desc: Vessel capable of carrying containers and other cargo.

9.name: Exceptional transport
9.desc:
Transport for which common characteristics are not applicable (e.g.
                                    big transformers requiring special wagons, special tackles, special routing etc.).

10.name: Bus
10.desc: To specify that the means of transportation is a bus.

11.name: Ship
11.desc: A large vessel navigating deep water.

12.name: Ship tanker
12.desc: A large vessel equipped to transport liquids.

13.name: Ocean vessel
13.desc: An ocean-going vessel that is not a ship.

15.name: Taxi
15.desc: A means of transport identification code indicating a taxi.

16.name: Barge
16.desc: A category of boat used to transport material over water.

17.name: Customer determined means of transport
17.desc: The type of means of transport is to be determined by the customer.

18.name: Seller determined means of transport
18.desc: The type of means of transport is to be determined by the seller.

19.name: Tip-up truck
19.desc: A truck capable of tipping up in order to deliver its load.

20.name: Furniture truck
20.desc: A truck used explicitly for the conveyance of furniture.

21.name: Rail tanker
21.desc: A rail wagon equipped to transport liquids.

23.name: Rail bulk car
23.desc: A rail wagon equipped to transport bulk cargo.

24.name: Customer rail tanker
24.desc: A customer-owned rail wagon equipped to transport liquids.

26.name: Tip-up articulated truck
26.desc:
An articulated truck capable of tipping up in order to deliver its
                                    load.

27.name: Rigid truck with tank
27.desc:
A rigid truck fitted with a tank capable of carrying liquids or bulk
                                    goods.

28.name: Refrigerated truck and trailer
28.desc:
A combined truck and trailer equipped to maintain refrigerated
                                    temperatures.

29.name: Freezer truck and trailer
29.desc:
A combined truck and trailer equipped to maintain freezing
                                    temperatures.

30.name:
Tautliner 25 tonne, combined with 90 cubic meter trailer with
                                    removable roof
30.desc:
A truck with non-ridged sides, 25 tonne capacity combined with a 90
                                    cubic meter trailer with removable roof.

31.name: Truck
31.desc: An automotive vehicle for hauling goods.

32.name: Road tanker
32.desc: An over-the-road tank trucker or trailer.

35.name: Truck/trailer with tilt
35.desc: A truck and trailer combination with a tilting capability.

36.name: Pipeline
36.desc: A line of pipes for conveying water, gas, oil, etc.

37.name: Hydrant cart
37.desc:
Vehicle used at large airports with installed distribution systems to
                                    make into-plane deliveries of fuel; distinguished from other types of fuelling
                                    vehicles.

39.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof
39.desc: A truck with non-ridged sides and removable roof.

40.name: Truck with opening floor
40.desc:
A truck with an opening floor mechanism which is used to discharge the
                                    cargo.

41.name: Freezer truck
41.desc: A truck equipped to maintain freezing temperatures.

42.name: Isothermic truck
42.desc: A truck equipped to maintain controlled temperatures.

43.name: Refrigerated truck
43.desc: A truck equipped to maintain refrigerated temperatures.

44.name: Freezer van
44.desc: A small rigid covered vehicle for conveying frozen goods.

45.name: Isothermic van
45.desc:
A small rigid covered vehicle for conveying temperature controlled
                                    goods.

46.name: Refrigerated van
46.desc: A small rigid covered vehicle for conveying refrigerated goods.

47.name: Bulk truck
47.desc: A truck suitable for transporting bulk goods.

48.name: Van
48.desc: A small vehicle suitable for carrying small volume loads.

49.name: Roadrailer
49.desc:
Used for shipments that travel by multimodal rail or highway trailer
                                    (roadrailer).

51.name: Cargo and passenger vessel
51.desc: Vessel for carrying cargo and passengers.

54.name: Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) carrier
54.desc: Vessel for carrying Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG).

55.name: Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG) carrier
55.desc: Vessel for carrying Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG).

57.name: Timber or log carrier
57.desc: Vessel for carrying timber or logs.

61.name: Cement vessel
61.desc: Vessel for carrying cement in bulk.

63.name: Ore carrier
63.desc: Vessel for carrying ore in bulk.

64.name: Car carrier
64.desc: Vessel for carrying complete cars and/or their knock- down parts.

66.name: Roll on - roll off vessel
66.desc: A vessel capable of carrying roll on - roll off cargo.

67.name: Ferry
67.desc:
A means of transport for carrying passengers and/or vehicles on a
                                    regular basis.

68.name: Fishing vessel
68.desc: Vessel used in the catching of fish.

69.name: Work vessel
69.desc:
A vessel engaged in 'port and harbour work', which means construction,
                                    improvement, maintenance or rehabilitation of port and harbour facilities. Dredger,
                                    floating crane, sand carrier with grab bucket are included in this type of the means
                                    of transport.

70.name: Patrol vessel
70.desc: A vessel to patrol port or coastal area.

71.name: Tug and/or push boat
71.desc: A vessel to push and/or pull other vessels.

72.name: Train with one wagon
72.desc: A train with a single wagon used to carry goods.

73.name: Train with more than one and less than 20 wagons
73.desc:
A train with more than one and less than 20 wagons used to carry
                                    goods.

74.name: Train with 20 or more wagons
74.desc: A train with 20 or more wagons used to carry goods.

75.name: Oil products tanker
75.desc: A vessel for carrying products derived from crude oil.

76.name: Training vessel
76.desc: A vessel for learning maritime skills.

77.name: Freezer truck and isothermic trailer
77.desc: A combined freezer truck and isothermic trailer.

78.name: Isothermic truck and isothermic trailer
78.desc: A truck and a trailer equipped to maintain controlled temperatures.

79.name: Refrigerated truck and isothermic trailer
79.desc: A combined refrigerated truck and isothermic trailer.

80.name: Freezer truck and refrigerated trailer
80.desc: A combined freezer truck and refrigerated trailer.

81.name: Isothermic truck and refrigerated trailer
81.desc: A combined isothermic truck and refrigerated trailer.

82.name: Rigid truck with tank and tank trailer
82.desc: A combined rigid truck with tank and tank trailer.

83.name: Bulk truck and tank trailer
83.desc:
A combined truck capable of carrying liquids or bulk goods and a tank
                                    trailer.

84.name: Rigid truck with tank and bulk trailer
84.desc:
A combined rigid truck with tank and a trailer capable of carrying
                                    liquids or bulk goods.

85.name: Bulk truck and bulk trailer
85.desc:
A combined truck and a trailer both capable of carrying liquids or
                                    bulk goods.

86.name: Tautliner truck and extendable trailer
86.desc: A combined tautliner truck and extendable trailer.

87.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof and extendable trailer
87.desc: A combined tautliner truck with removable roof and extendable trailer.

88.name: Truck with opening floor and extendable trailer
88.desc: A combined truck with opening floor and extendable trailer.

89.name: Bulk truck and extendable trailer
89.desc:
A combined truck capable of carrying liquids or bulk goods and an
                                    extendable trailer.

90.name: Isothermic truck and freezer trailer
90.desc: A combined isothermic truck and freezer trailer.

91.name: Refrigerated truck and freezer trailer
91.desc: A combined refrigerated truck and freezer trailer.

92.name: Tip-up truck and gondola trailer
92.desc:
A combined tip-up truck and gondola trailer. A gondola trailer is a
                                    split level trailer suitable for the transport of heavy machinery.

93.name: Tautliner truck and gondola trailer
93.desc:
A combined tautliner truck and gondola trailer. A gondola trailer is a
                                    split level trailer suitable for the transport of heavy machinery.

94.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof and gondola trailer
94.desc:
A combined tautliner truck with removable roof and gondola trailer. A
                                    gondola trailer is a split level trailer suitable for the transport of heavy
                                    machinery.

95.name: Truck with opening floor and gondola trailer
95.desc:
A combined truck with opening floor and gondola trailer. A gondola
                                    trailer is a split level trailer suitable for the transport of heavy machinery.

96.name: Bulk truck and gondola trailer
96.desc:
A combined truck capable of carrying liquids or bulk goods and a
                                    gondola trailer. A gondola trailer is a split level trailer suitable for the
                                    transport of heavy machinery.

97.name: Tip-up truck and extendable gondola trailer
97.desc:
A combined tip-up truck with extendable gondola trailer. An extendable
                                    gondola trailer is a trailer fitted with a rear axle which can be extended to cater
                                    for variable length and is suitable for the transport of heavy machinery.

98.name: Tautliner truck and extendable gondola trailer
98.desc:
A combined tautliner truck and extendable gondola trailer. An
                                    extendable gondola trailer is a trailer fitted with a rear axle which can be
                                    extended to cater for variable length and is suitable for the transport of heavy
                                    machinery.

99.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof and extendable gondola trailer
99.desc:
A combined tautliner truck with removable roof and extendable gondola
                                    trailer. An extendable gondola trailer is a trailer fitted with a rear axle which
                                    can be extended to cater for variable length and is suitable for the transport of
                                    heavy machinery.

100.name: Truck with opening floor and extendable gondola trailer
100.desc:
A combined truck with opening floor and extendable gondola trailer. An
                                    extendable gondola trailer is a trailer fitted with a rear axle which can be
                                    extended to cater for variable length and is suitable for the transport of heavy
                                    machinery.

101.name: Bulk truck and extendable gondola trailer
101.desc:
A combined truck capable of carrying liquids or bulk goods and a
                                    extendable gondola trailer. An extendable gondola trailer is a trailer fitted with a
                                    rear axle which can be extended to cater for variable length and is suitable for the
                                    transport of heavy machinery.

102.name: Tip-up truck and trailer with opening floor
102.desc: A combined tip-up truck and trailer with opening floor.

103.name: Tautliner truck and trailer with opening floor
103.desc: A combined tautliner truck and trailer with opening floor.

104.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof and trailer with opening floor
104.desc:
A combined tautliner truck with removable roof and trailer with
                                    opening floor.

105.name: Truck and trailer with opening floor
105.desc: A combined truck and a trailer with an opening floor.

106.name: Bulk truck and trailer with opening floor
106.desc:
A combined truck capable of carrying liquids or bulk goods and a
                                    trailer with opening floor.

107.name: Removal truck and trailer
107.desc: A combined truck and trailer capable of carrying household effects.

108.name: Tautliner truck and removal trailer
108.desc:
A combined tautliner truck and trailer capable of carrying household
                                    effects.

109.name: Tautliner truck with removable roof and removal trailer
109.desc:
A combined tautliner truck with a removable roof and a trailer capable
                                    of carrying household effects.

110.name: Vessel, temperature controlled cargo
110.desc: A vessel to carry temperature controlled cargo.
